  "text": "The sample size used in this study was relatively small, reducing the power of the study to detect significant differences between groups. This is of particular relevance when considering the null findings for amygdala and prefrontal regions. The sample size was, however, comparable to, or greater than, samples reported in other studies of face and emotion processing in autism [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
